						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold deposited with the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Nāṅgūr for the principal offering (of rice) during the day's worship to god Tiruveṇkāḍa-Dēvar and to feed one person therewith in the temple, by <hi rend="bold">Naṟumān Kiḻāṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Maṇiśivaṉ</hi> a merchant of <hi rend="bold">Ādirāyamaṅgalyapuram</hi> in Mēṟkā-nāḍu, the same as the present <hi rend="bold">Tīruvadi</hi> in the Cuddalore taluk.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
